===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
Possibly the original character of {{och-l|旁|side}}, with its form related to {{och-l|巫}}. {{zh-l|巫}} depicts four extremities with indicator symbols, being the original character of {{och-l|荒}} in {{zh-l|四荒}}. Compared to {{och-l|巫}}, one end of this character lacks the indicator symbol and is elongated to denote "side" {{och-l|旁}}. {{och-l|方}} in {{zh-l|四方}} and {{och-l|荒}} in {{zh-l|四荒}} may be cognates.<ref>鄔可晶：《據出土本說〈老子〉第四十一章“大方無隅”等句》，“早期寫本與《老子》新研”學術研討會，2023年。</ref>

It is unrelated to {{och-l|㫃|gloss=fluttering flag}}, from which characters like {{och-l|旗|gloss=flag}} and {{och-l|旅|gloss=troops}} are derived.

===Etymology 1===
; "side; square; region"
: Probably related to {{och-l|旁}}, {{och-l|傍}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).
; "parallel boats"
: Cognate with {{och-l|舫|gloss=boat}}, {{och-l|艕|gloss=boat}}. According to STEDT, from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*poŋ||raft; float}}; compare {{cog|my|ဖောင်||raft}}, {{cog|kac|hpong||kac}}. According to {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}}, this etymon is an area word; compare {{cog|th|พ่วง||raft; pontoon}}, {{cog|map-pro|*qabaŋ||boat}}, {{cog|omx||kɓaŋ|ship; boat}}.
; "just now"; "now"
: Cognate with {{och-l|甫|gloss=just now}}. Compare {{cog|kac|hpang||to begin}}, {{cog|tbq-kuk-pro|*pran||to begin}} (STEDT).
; "method; law"
: Etymology not certain. May be the same word as {{och-l|方|gloss=side; square; region|id=1}}. Cognate with {{och-l|仿|gloss=to imitate}}. Perhaps cognate with {{cog|bo|བྱང་བ||skill; experience}}, {{cog|bo|སྦྱངས||trained; exercised studied}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Alternatively, it may belong to {{cog|km|ព្រាង||to draft; to sketch}} < {{cog|km|រាង||shape; form; figure}}. If so, it belongs to an Austroasiatic allofam which includes {{och-l|狀|gloss=form; appearance}}. "Law; norm; standard" is a common extension of "form; shape".

